les on Arabic Literature Published in 1992’</span> <i><span n="33733">Journal</span> <span n="33734">of</span> <span n="33735">Arabic</span> <span n="33736">Literature</span></i><span n="33737">, Vol. XXIV, 1993, E.J. Brill, Leiden.</span></span></div></li><li><div class="paragraph-block"><span dir="ltr" class="align_left"><span n="33738">Farid, Maher Shafiq. ‘A Bibliography of Modern Egyptian Literature in English Translation’, in</span> <i><span n="33739">The</span> <span n="33740">Comparative</span> <span n="33741">Tone:</span> <span n="33742">Essays</span> <span n="33743">in</span> <span n="33744">Comparative</span> <span n="33745">Literature</span></i><span n="33746">, ed. M.M. Enani, State Publishing House (GEBO), 1995.</span></span></div></li><li><div class="paragraph-block"><span dir="ltr" class="align_left"><span n="33747">Hafez, Sabry. ‘A Complete Bibliography of Collections of Egyptian Short Stories (1921–1970)’,</span> <i><span n="33748">Journal</span> <span n="33749">of</span> <span n="33750">Arabic</span> <span n="33751">Literature</span></i><span n="33752">, Vol. XI, 1980, E.J. Brill, Leiden, pp. 123–138.</span></span></div></li><li><div class="paragraph-block"><span dir="ltr" class="align_left"><span n="33753">Sakkout, Hamdi (ed.) ‘The Modern Arabic Novel:</span> <i><span n="33754">Bibliography</span> <span n="33755">and</span> <span n="33756">Critical</span> <span n="33757">Introduction</span></i> <span n="33758">1865–1995’, National Library Press, Cairo, 1998, reprinted by The American University in Cairo Press, 2000 in 5 volumes.</span></span></div></li><li><div class="paragraph-block"><span dir="ltr" class="align_left"><span n="33759">Samaan, Angele Botros.</span> <i><span n="33760">Arabic</span> <span n="33761">Literature</span> <span n="33762">in</span> <span n="33763">Egypt</span> <span n="33764">in</span> <span n="33765">English</span> <span n="33766">Translation:</span> <span n="33767">A</span> <span n="33768">Bibliography</span></i><span n=